body: that is tensorflow shit. IDK how to fix

It seems to be working now, though I have to be careful to lower batch sizes during Xseg or SAEHD. I did several things at once so I can't say that did a great job troubleshooting, but it seems what did it was to uninstall Python from my computer. It seems to run Python from within the DFL folder structure. 

So I'm not entirely sure why it's working now and I'm a bit confused because uninstalling Python doesn't seem on the surface like it should be effected by the size of your paging file.

Yea I agree that makes no sense.
Would you be able to list down all the things you did so maybe we can discuss what might have caused the problem?
same thing. and i dont have python installed

I'm having the same issues on my new PC with a fresh Windows 10 install and a RTX 3090.
The strange part is, that DFL (exact same copy of build_01_04_2021) runs just fine with the same GPU on my old system (also Win 10 20H2 Build 19042.746).
But there is also a ton of other Software installed, some related to other ML software, as well as Python, CUDA 10.0 with cuDNN.
I only have this one GPU to test with so this may take a while, but I just made logs with ProcMon to see what DFL does different.

Right of the bet I noticed that Python/DFL is accessing files in "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v10.0\" which does not happen on the "not-working" machine (because I have not -yet- installed it).

Training Quick96 and SAEHD are working

//edit
After installing CUDA 10.0 for Windows 10 (cuda_10.0.130_411.31_win10) + cuDNN (cudnn-10.0-windows10-x64-v7.6.5.32) and rebooting, the issue is gone for me.
tried installing the CUDA 10 and cuDNN still get the same error
